{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Given G and a natural language question q, the task of KGQA is to extract a set of entities {a q } ∈ G that correctly answer q.",
    "Following previous works (Lan et al., 2022), question-answer pairs are given for training, but not the ground-truth paths that lead to the answers.",
    "As KGs usually contain millions of facts and nodes, a smaller question-specific subgraph G q is retrieved for a question q.",
    "Entity linking identifies question entities {e q } and subgraph G q is extracted by following connections that start from these question entities (Yih et al., 2015).",
    "Ideally, all correct answers for the question are contained in the retrieved subgraph, {a q } ∈ G q."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Following previous works (Lan et al., 2022), question-answer pairs are given for training, but not the ground-truth paths that lead to the answers.",
    "Entity linking identifies question entities {e q } and subgraph G q is extracted by following connections that start from these question entities (Yih et al., 2015)."
  ]
}